      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tool-result): increase default max tool result chars for larger payloads",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen using `nodes invoke` with `screen.snapshot`, the base64-encoded PNG payload (~25K chars for 1920x1280) gets truncated at 16K, making the screenshot unusable.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Increased `DEFAULT_MAX_LIVE_TOOL_RESULT_CHARS` from 16K to 32K\n- Increased `LARGE_CONTEXT_MAX_LIVE_TOOL_RESULT_CHARS` from 32K to 64K\n\nThis allows larger tool result payloads (base64 screenshots, long file outputs) to pass through without truncation.\n\nCloses #94280\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** base64 screenshot payloads truncated at 16K chars, making them invalid.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Code change validated at source level - the constant change is the only limiting factor for tool result size.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Changed constants ensure 25K+ payloads pass through without head+tail truncation.\n\n**What was not tested:** Not tested against a live Windows node with screen.snapshot.",
